{"title_page": "Thomas Lewis (footballer)", "text_new": "{{short description|Welsh footballer}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n|name           = Thomas Lewis\n|image          =\n| image_size     =\n|caption        =\n|fullname       =\n|birth_date     =\n|birth_place    = Wales\n|death_date     = <!--{{death date and age|||||||df=yes}}-->\n|death_place    =\n|height         =\n|position       =\n|youthyears1    =\n|youthclubs1    =\n|years1         = 1880\u20131881\n|clubs1         = [[Wrexham A.F.C.|Wrexham]]\n|caps1          =\n|goals1         =\n|years2         =\n|clubs2         =\n|caps2          =\n|goals2         =\n|totalcaps      =\n|totalgoals     =\n|nationalyears1 = 1881\n|nationalteam1  = [[Wales national football team|Wales]]\n|nationalcaps1  = 2\n|nationalgoals1 = 0\n| manageryears1  =\n| managerclubs1  =\n| medaltemplates =\n}}\n'''Thomas Lewis ''' was a [[Welsh people|Welsh]] international [[association football|footballer]]. He was part of the [[Wales national football team]], playing 2 matches. He played his first match on 26 February 1881 against England and his last match on 14 March 1881 against Scotland.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://eu-football.info/_players.php?id=218|title=Wales player database 1872 to 2013|publisher=eu-football.info|accessdate=30 April 2016}}</ref>\n\nAt club level, he played for [[Wrexham A.F.C.|Wrexham]] from 1880\u20131881.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldfootball.net/player_summary/thomas-lewis |title=Thomas Lewis |publisher=worldfootball.net |accessdate=24 October 2017}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of Wales international footballers (alphabetical)]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2017}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lewis, Thomas}}\n[[Category:Welsh footballers]]\n[[Category:Wales international footballers]]\n[[Category:Wrexham A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Place of birth missing]]\n[[Category:Year of death missing]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing]]\n[[Category:Association footballers not categorized by position]]\n\n\n{{Wales-footy-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Welsh footballer}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n|name           = Thomas Lewis\n|image          =\n| image_size     =\n|caption        =\n|fullname       =\n|birth_date     =\n|birth_place    = Wales\n|death_date     = <!--{{death date and age|||||||df=yes}}-->\n|death_place    =\n|height         =\n|position       =\n|youthyears1    =\n|youthclubs1    =\n|years1         = 1880\u20131881\n|clubs1         = [[Wrexham A.F.C.|Wrexham]]\n|caps1          =\n|goals1         =\n|years2         =\n|clubs2         =\n|caps2          =\n|goals2         =\n|totalcaps      =\n|totalgoals     =\n|nationalyears1 = 1881\n|nationalteam1  = [[Wales national football team|Wales]]\n|nationalcaps1  = 2\n|nationalgoals1 = 0\n| manageryears1  =\n| managerclubs1  =\n| medaltemplates =\n}}\n'''Thomas Lewis ''' was a [[Welsh people|Welsh]] international [[association football|footballer]]. He was part of the [[Wales national football team]], playing 2 matches. He played his first match on 26 February 1881 against England and his last match on 14 March 1881 against Scotland.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://eu-football.info/_players.php?id=218|title=Wales player database 1872 to 2013|publisher=eu-football.info|accessdate=30 April 2016}}</ref>\n\nAt club level, he played for [[Wrexham A.F.C.|Wrexham]] from 1880-1881.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldfootball.net/player_summary/thomas-lewis |title=Thomas Lewis |publisher=worldfootball.net |accessdate=24 October 2017}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of Wales international footballers (alphabetical)]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2017}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lewis, Thomas}}\n[[Category:Welsh footballers]]\n[[Category:Wales international footballers]]\n[[Category:Wrexham A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Place of birth missing]]\n[[Category:Year of death missing]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing]]\n\n\n[[Category:Association footballers not categorized by position]]\n{{Wales-footy-bio-stub}}\n", "name_user": "GiantSnowman", "label": "safe", "comment": "clean up,typo(s) fixed: 1880-1881 \u2192 1880\u20131881", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thomas_Lewis_(footballer)"}
{"title_page": "GamePigeon", "text_new": "{{Infobox software\n| name = GamePigeon\n| logo = \n| logo alt = \n| logo caption = \n| screenshot = \n| screenshot size =\n| screenshot alt = \n| caption = \n| collapsible = <!-- Any text here will collapse the screenshot. -->\n| author = \n| developer = Vitalii Zlotskii\n| released = {{Start date and age|2016|09|13|df=yes/no}} \n| discontinued = <!-- Set to yes if software is discontinued, otherwise omit. -->\n| ver layout = <!-- simple (default) or stacked -->\n| latest release version = \n| latest release date = <!-- {{Start date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|df=yes/no}} -->\n| latest preview version = \n| latest preview date = <!-- {{Start date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|df=yes/no}} -->\n| repo = <!-- {{URL|example.org}} -->\n| programming language = \n| engine = <!-- or engines -->\n| operating system = \n| platform = \n| included with = \n| size = 113.8 MB\n| language = \n| language count = <!-- Number only -->\n| language footnote = \n| genre = \n| license = \n| alexa = \n| website = <!-- {{URL|example.org}} -->\n| standard = \n| AsOf = \n}}\n\n'''GamePigeon''' is a gaming [[mobile app]] for [[iOS]] devices. The app was launched by the company Vitalii Zlotskii,<ref name=Takahashi2016>{{cite web|last=Takahashi|first=Dean|url=https://venturebeat.com/2016/10/20/mastermind-studios-launches-battle-bash-strategy-game-on-imessage/|title=Mastermind Studios launches Battle Bash strategy game on iMessage|work=[[VentureBeat]]|date=October 20, 2016|accessdate=April 4, 2020}}</ref> on September 13, 2016, as a result of the [[iOS 10]] update which expanded how users could interact with the [[Messages (Apple)|Messages app]].<ref name=Siegal2016>{{cite web|last=Siegal|first=Jacob|url=https://bgr.com/2016/09/13/ios-10-best-apps-games-stickers/|title=10 of the best iMessage apps, games and stickers for iOS 10 on launch day|work=[[Boy Genius Report]]|date=September 13, 2016|accessdate=April 4, 2020}}</ref><ref name=Bond2020/> Thus, users could access and play on the GamePigeon app within the iMessage app.<ref name=Siegal2016/>\n\n==Development and release==\nThe app was released on September 13, 2016, coinciding with the launch of [[iOS 10]].<ref name=Bond2020/> The app was released for free,<ref name=Johnson2018>{{cite web|last=Johnson|first=Khari|url=https://venturebeat.com/2018/03/05/google-search-results-now-available-in-apples-imessage-app-drawer/|title=Google search results now available in Apple's iMessage app drawer|work=[[VentureBeat]]|date=March 5, 2018|accessdate=April 4, 2020}}</ref> although it includes in-app purchases to unlock additional items, such as [[Cue stick|pool cues]].<ref name=Dirks2019>{{cite web|last=Dirks|first=Brent|url=https://www.makeuseof.com/tag/imessage-games-play-with-friends/|title= 9 Best iMessage Games and How to Play Them With Your Friends|work=MakeUseOf|date=December 7, 2019|accessdate=April 4, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Games in the app==\nThe following is a list of games which users can play within GamePigeon:\n{{Col-begin}}\n{{Col-break}}\n*[[Eight-ball|8 Ball]]\n*[[Nine-ball|9 Ball]]\n*20 Questions\n*Anagrams\n*Archery\n*Basketball\n*[[Draughts|Checkers]]\n*[[Chess]]\n*[[Crazy Eights|Crazy 8]]\n*[[Beer pong|Cup Pong]]\n*Darts\n*[[Dots and Boxes|Dots & Boxes]]\n{{Col-break}}\n*Filler\n*[[Connect Four|Four In A Row]]\n*[[Gomoku]]\n*Knockout\n*[[Mancala]]\n*Mini Golf\n*Paintball\n*[[Reversi]]\n*[[Battleship (game)|Sea Battle]]\n*[[Shuffleboard]]\n*Tanks\n*Word Hunt\n{{Col-end}}\n<small>Sources:<ref name=AppStore/><ref name=WPST2020>{{cite web|url=https://wpst.com/cup-pong-social-distancing/|title=Here's How I'm Hosting a \"Social Distancing Cup Pong Tournament\" This Weekend|publisher=[[WPST]]|date=2020|accessdate=April 4, 2020}}</ref><ref name=Chokkattu2017/></small>\n\nIn 2016, [[Poker]] was cited as one of the games included in GamePigeon,<ref name=Vorhees2016>{{cite web|last=Vorhees|first=John|url=https://www.macstories.net/roundups/my-favorite-imessage-apps-and-sticker-packs-of-2016/|title=My Favorite iMessage Apps and Sticker Packs of 2016|website=MacStories.net|date=December 23, 2016|accessdate=April 4, 2020}}</ref><ref name=Pullen2016/> although it is not listed on the game's App Store description.<ref name=AppStore/>\n\n==Reception==\nGamePigeon has enjoyed commercial success, with [[VentureBeat]] noting that GamePigeon was ranked number-one in the \"Top Free\" category of the iMessage App Store, six months after its release.<ref name=Johnson2017>{{cite web|last=Johnson|first=Khari|url=https://venturebeat.com/2017/03/20/forget-stickers-imessages-top-15-apps-and-games/|title=Forget stickers: iMessage\u2019s top 15 apps and games|work=[[VentureBeat]]|date=March 20, 2017|accessdate=April 4, 2020}}</ref> Critically, GamePigeon has been generally well received, being highlighted by online media publications early on shortly after the iOS 10 launch.<ref name=Pullen2016>{{cite web|last=Pullen|first=John Patrick|url=https://time.com/4534887/apple-messages-imessage-tips-tricks/|title=The Ultimate Guide to Apple's New Messages App|work=[[Time (magazine)|Time]]|date=October 18, 2016|accessdate=April 4, 2020}}</ref> It has since been included on many \"best iMessage apps\" lists.<ref name=Bond2020/><ref name=Chokkattu2017>{{cite web|last=Chokkattu|first=Julian|url=https://www.digitaltrends.com/mobile/best-imessage-apps-games-stickers/|title=Own an iPhone 7? Try these 15 iMessage apps, sticker packs, games for iOS 10|work=[[Digital Trends]]|date=August 18, 2017|accessdate=April 4, 2020}}</ref><ref name=Johnson2017/> Based on over 88,000 ratings, the game holds a 4.2 out of 5 rating on the [[App Store (iOS)|App Store]].<ref name=AppStore>{{cite web|url=https://apps.apple.com/us/app/gamepigeon/id1124197642|title=GamePigeon on the App Store|publisher=[[Apple Inc.]]|accessdate=April 4, 2020}}</ref> Julian Chokkattu of ''[[Digital Trends]]'' wrote \"GamePigeon should be like the pre-installed versions of Solitaire and Minesweeper that used to come with older iterations of Windows.\"<ref name=Chokkattu2017/> On its launch day, [[Boy Genius Report]] included it on a list of \"10 of the best iMessage apps, games and stickers for iOS 10 on launch day.\"<ref name=Siegal2016/> ''[[The Daily Dot]]'' wrote, \"GamePigeon is easily the best current gaming option within iMessages.\"<ref name=Bond2020/>\n\n8-Ball and Cup Pong have been particularly well-received by media outlets.<ref name=Bell2019>{{cite web|last=Bell|first=Killian|url=https://www.cultofmac.com/649048/apple-has-no-plans-to-scrap-imessage-apps-and-games/|title=Apple has no plans to scrap iMessage apps and games|website=[[The Cult of Mac|cultofmac.com]]|date=September 3, 2019|accessdate=April 4, 2020}}</ref> ''The Daily Dot'' had specific praise for the app's [[billiards]] game: \"8-Ball controls shockingly smoothly with your fingers, and there\u2019s nothing quite like destroying a dear friend in poker.\"<ref name=Bond2020>{{cite web|last=Bond|first=John-Michael|url=https://www.dailydot.com/debug/best-free-apps-imessages/|title=Text like a champ with these 5 free apps for iMessages|work=[[The Daily Dot]]|date=February 28, 2020|accessdate=April 4, 2020}}</ref> During his [[Cory Booker 2020 presidential campaign|2020 U.S. presidential campaign]], [[Cory Booker]] was cited as playing the game with his family.<ref name=EOL2019>{{cite web|url=https://www.eonline.com/news/1056958/2020-presidential-democratic-candidates-reveal-their-pop-culture-favorites|title= 2020 Presidential Democratic Candidates Reveal Their Pop Culture Favorites |work=[[E!#E! Online|E! Online]]|date=July 18, 2019|accessdate=April 4, 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, [[CNBC]] cited one teenager who expressed that GamePigeon was one of just a few reasons that [[Generation Z|those in her age range]] use the iMessage app.<ref name=Castillo2017>{{cite web|last=Castillo|first=Michelle|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2017/02/28/teen-internet-habits-instagram-snapchat-facebook-privacy.html|title=Teens explain how they really use Snapchat and Instagram, and why Facebook still matters|publisher=[[CNBC]]|date=February 28, 2017|accessdate=April 4, 2020}}</ref> The game has received particular positive reception for allowing introverted individuals to exercise a form social activity; similarly, the game was highlighted as a way to maintain [[social distancing]] guidelines during the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]].<ref name=WPST2020/><ref name=Rao2020>{{cite web|last=Rao|first=Emma|url=https://tuftsdaily.com/features/2020/03/10/revisiting-introversion-extroversion-learning-part-2/|title= Revisiting introversion and extroversion: Learning from each other, part 2|work=[[The Tufts Daily]]|date=March 10, 2020|accessdate=April 4, 2020}}</ref><ref name=Webb2020>{{cite web|last=Webb|first=Jack|url=https://www.standard.co.uk/tech/imessage-games-how-find-play-iphone-a4396311.html|title=People are reviving iMessage games during self-isolation - here's how to find them|work=[[Evening Standard]]|date=March 24, 2020|accessdate=April 4, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Influence==\n[[Snapchat]] released an in-message games app called Snapchat Games.<ref name=Sherrill2020>{{cite web|last=Sherrill|first=Cameron|url=https://www.esquire.com/lifestyle/g31990231/best-mobile-games-2020/|title=The 15 Best Mobile Games to Wile Away Hour After Hour Playing in 2020|work=[[Esquire (magazine)|Esquire]]|date=March 31, 2020|accessdate=April 4, 2020}}</ref>\n\nFor an [[April Fools' Day]] joke, ''[[The Chronicle (Duke University)|The Chronicle]]'', a [[Duke University]] newspaper, published that [[Duke Blue Devils|Duke's athletic program]] adopted Cup Pong as an official varsity sport.<ref name=Duke2020>{{cite web|url=https://www.dukechronicle.com/article/2020/04/duke-athletics-game-pigeon-cup-pong-varsity-sport|title=Duke Athletics adds GamePigeon 'Cup Pong' as official varsity sport|work=[[The Chronicle (Duke University)|The Chronicle]]|date=April 1, 2020|accessdate=April 4, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em