alo]], ([[Philippines]]),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/nation/09/04/09/sept-7-21-declared-non-working-holidays |title=Sept 7, 21 declared non-working holidays |publisher=ABS-CBN News |date=2009-09-06 |accessdate=2016-07-15}}</ref>\n*[[Sister L\u00facia]], (Portugal)\n*[[Mother Teresa of Calcutta]], (mainly India, Albania, and some Roman Catholic countries)\n*[[Maxim of Bulgaria|Patriarch Maxim of Bulgaria]] ([[Bulgaria]])\n*[[Serbian Patriarch Pavle]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.b92.net/eng/news/politics-article.php?yyyy=2009&mm=11&dd=16&nav_id=63065 |title=Serbia observes first day of mourning |publisher=B92 |date=2009-11-16 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110608081557/http://www.b92.net/eng/news/politics-article.php?yyyy=2009&mm=11&dd=16&nav_id=63065 |archivedate=2011-06-08}}</ref>\n*[[Pope John Paul II]], (many countries including [[Egypt]], [[Hungary]], [[Cuba]] (three days), [[Italy]], [[Ireland]], [[Seychelles]], [[Malawi]], the [[Republic of the Congo]], the [[Democratic Republic of Congo]], [[Portugal]] (three days), [[Brazil]], [[Poland]] (seven days), [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]], [[Mexico]], [[Spain]], the [[Czech Republic]] and [[Slovenia]])<ref>{{cite news |last1=McFadden |first1=Robert D. |title=In Many Lands and Tongues, Remembering Pope as Minister of Peace |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2005/04/04/world/europe/in-many-lands-and-tongues-remembering-pope-as-minister-of.html |accessdate=9 January 2020 |work=[[The New York Times]] |date=4 April 2005}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=World Mourns Pope John Paul II - Novinite.com - Sofia News Agency |url=https://www.novinite.com/articles/46319/World+Mourns+Pope+John+Paul+II |accessdate=9 January 2020 |work=www.novinite.com |date=April 3, 2005}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=World mourns Pope John Paul II |url=http://www.nbcnews.com/id/7357164/ns/world_news-one_year_later_remembering_pope_john_paul_ii/t/world-mourns-pope-john-paul-ii/#.Xhc15Mg3mM8 |accessdate=9 January 2020 |publisher=